{{Quote|When they booked Diahann Carol, I said, 'Why is Diahann Carol on this?' and they said, 'Well, because of the name and the network wants black people.' Also, I think there was some controversy at that point about ''Star Wars'' not having black people in it. So I said, 'Well, now what do we do with Diahann Carol?!'|[[David Acomba]]|<ref name="script and directors">{{SWArchive|url=movies/saga/20081117.html|text=Holiday Special: Script and Directors}}</ref>}}
'''Diahann Carroll''' (d. [[October 4]], [[2019]]) was an actress and singer. She portrayed the "Holographic Wow" known as [[Mermeia]], which was the subject of [[Attichitcuk/Legends|Attichitcuk's]] sexual fantasies in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''.

==Biography==
On [[October 4]], [[2019]], Carroll died in Los Angeles, California of cancer at the age of 84.<ref name="Death" />

